Package com.github.yeetmanlord.bedwars_zeta.api.api_event_hooks.data

Class MenuItemReadEvent

java.lang.Object
org.bukkit.event.Event
com.github.yeetmanlord.bedwars_zeta.api.api_event_hooks.data.MenuItemReadEvent
public class MenuItemReadEvent extends Event
This is for adding new custom menu items. This can also be used to override default menu items. By menu items I mean items that are part of configurable bedwars menus, mainly the upgrade and shop menus.
Author:
YeetManLord
API Example:
public void event (MenuItemReadEvent event) {

    if (event.function.equals("my_custom_function_name") && event.type == ItemReadType.UPGRADE) {

      int arg0 = (int) event.getData().get("arg_0"); event.setItem(new MyCustomItem(base.getDisplayStack(), EnumUpgradeMenuItemFunction.CUSTOM, event.base.getSlot(), event.base.getPageNum() {Any other args})
    }
If you have more than one custom event then add else ifs if the event id doesn't match any of your events do nothing DO NOT USE event.setItem(null) as it may break other extensions/apis for this plugin

* For a custom ShopItem you would use EnumShopItemFunction.CUSTOM instead!
